translated: Eksell, Gustaf Erik, district judge, Skara. Born on July 14, 1894 in Kisa, Östergötland, the first of the factory owner Levin E. and Hildegard Dju-lang's children. Married to Tyra Strandeli in 1920, with whom he had four children: Bengt (born in 1921), Mait (1923), Lisbeth (1925), and Anders (1928). He earned his high school degree in Linköping in 1912 and graduated with a degree in law from Stockholm University in 1916. He served as a court clerk in the Ovansiljan and Falu districts from 1917-1922 and as the first councilman in Skara from 1922-1928. He became mayor of Skara in 1928, which also made him a public notary. In 1940, he was appointed district judge of Skarabygden. Between 1922-1940, he served as chairman of the construction committee, was a member of the county council and its management committee from 1939, chairman of the wartime management committee in 1939, chairman of the Skaraborg County Savings Bank in 1941, chairman of the Skaraborg and Älvsborg County Savings Bank Association in 1942, a member of the commission responsible for the revision of terms for leasing purposes in various counties in 1942, and a member of the arbitration commission according to the Railway Traffic Act. He was on the board of directors for Skara's School for the Disabled, the Friends of Skara Cathedral Association, the West Gothland Tourist Traffic Association, the West Gothland Antiquities Association, and the Swedish Savings Bank Association in 1946. He received the Royal Order of the North Star and the Royal Victorian Order.
